RewardText: When the east wind blows let it send your fragrance, oh plum blossoms\nAlthough your master is gone, do not forget the spring
When the east wind blows let it send your fragrance, oh plum blossoms\nAlthough your master is gone, do not forget the spring
On this journey, I have no streamers made of silk to offer up\nGods, if it pleases you,may you take instead this beautiful brocade of autumn leaves
